      "rationale": "The primary validation QoI is normalised index of hemolysis (NIH), which is algebraically transformed to the relative hemolysis index (RH) used in the regulatory acceptance criterion. The transformation is monotonic and preserves rank ordering of operating conditions, ensuring that validation of NIH directly supports the COU decision."
    },
